  "prompt": "Why did Arnab Goswami left ET now?",
  "response": "Arnab Goswami left ET Now, where he was the editor-in-chief, in 2016 to launch his own news channel, Republic TV. His departure was part of a broader effort to create a media platform that he felt was more aligned with his vision for journalism, particularly in relation to political discourse in India. Goswami's move was also influenced by his desire to have greater control over editorial content and to pursue a format that emphasized more aggressive reporting and debate. His exit from ET Now marked a significant shift in the Indian media landscape, as he became known for his confrontational style and polarizing approach to news coverage.",
